Come on.

03:47.416 --> 03:48.416
Careful.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.208
I think your girlfriend
wants sunglasses now.

06:59.291 --> 07:01.791
No? Sunglasses for the beautiful woman.

07:31.958 --> 07:34.666
Can you take care of Thanasis?

07:34.750 --> 07:36.416


07:36.500 --> 07:37.500
Please.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.166
-Yes, of course.
-I need to go to hospital.

07:41.250 --> 07:42.375
Okay.

08:41.833 --> 08:43.541
-Is he okay?
-Yes.

08:44.291 --> 08:46.375
He is healthy and all clean.

08:46.958 --> 08:48.125
He's perfect.

08:48.625 --> 08:51.458
Is there any way
to contact your husband, Veronica?

08:51.958 --> 08:55.000
Uh, he's working in Árgos.
There's no telephone.

08:55.083 --> 08:56.416
He's going to get a surprise.

08:56.500 --> 08:59.000
Yes, he will.

08:59.083 --> 09:03.708
I just need some more information for the,
uh, Universal Health Service paperwork.

09:03.791 --> 09:06.083
I can never remember it.

09:06.166 --> 09:09.083
It's okay.
I will take a copy of your residency card.

09:09.166 --> 09:12.083
It's at home.
I was at work when I went into labor.

09:14.291 --> 09:15.625
Okay.

09:19.666 --> 09:20.666
Here.

10:42.958 --> 10:44.541
How was your trip?

10:48.125 --> 10:49.125
Very long.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.250
How have things been here?

10:55.416 --> 10:56.500
Oh, uneventful.

11:07.791 --> 11:08.791
Vera?

11:19.625 --> 11:22.208
You only have to think about
what's in front of you.

11:24.250 --> 11:25.500
Vera, I have another son.

11:38.083 --> 11:41.041
Thanasis Rotimi,
look at your baby brother.

11:41.625 --> 11:43.583
Look at your baby brother. Look.

11:44.958 --> 11:47.125
Friends come and go, but family's forever.

11:47.708 --> 11:48.791
You hear me?

11:48.875 --> 11:51.750
-Huh?
-You will never be alone.

11:58.750 --> 12:00.416
What shall you call him?

12:01.541 --> 12:05.375
Giannis. In Greek, it means "John,"
like the apostle.

12:06.333 --> 12:09.583
And Ugo in Ibo means "a crown."

12:10.583 --> 12:13.083
A crown that God has given,
nobody can take away.

12:13.166 --> 12:14.666
-Amen.
-Amen.

12:14.750 --> 12:16.458
-Amen.
-Amen.

12:43.291 --> 12:45.250
Sorry. You misspelled our last name.

12:47.458 --> 12:50.375
-There's too many letters.
-"Antetokounmpo."

12:50.458 --> 12:51.958
Adetokunbo.

12:52.541 --> 12:54.541
Antetokounmpo?

12:54.625 --> 12:56.500
-Adetokunbo.
-Excuse me, Ms. Pantazis?

12:56.583 --> 12:57.833
Tell them I'll be a minute.

12:57.916 --> 13:01.208
Are you sure we got it wrong?
Our translators are usually very good.

13:03.333 --> 13:05.958
We know our own name, Ms. Pantazis.

13:06.041 --> 13:08.916
It's Adetokunbo.
It's a very proud Yoruba name.

13:09.000 --> 13:12.125
It means "the king from across
the seas has returned."

13:12.208 --> 13:14.375
Okay, I'll make a note of it.

13:15.333 --> 13:18.166
Uh, did you bring your education history
and proof of current employment?

13:18.250 --> 13:19.250
Oh, yes.

13:19.333 --> 13:23.333
Uh, so, this is a letter
from the temp agency that gets us jobs.

13:30.833 --> 13:31.875
This isn't enough.

13:32.833 --> 13:35.875
You need to prove you're working legally,
on payroll.

13:36.875 --> 13:38.833
If you file
a residency application like this,

13:38.916 --> 13:42.416
it will be rejected on the basis
you entered Greece without permission.

13:42.500 --> 13:44.041
But we didn't choose to be illegal.

13:44.125 --> 13:47.875
Our passports were illegally confiscated
by the European police.

13:47.958 --> 13:50.750
We couldn't go back
because we had spent all of our savings.

13:50.833 --> 13:52.916
We had to cross the border.
You understand?

13:53.750 --> 13:56.916
Now, our boys are Greek.

13:58.791 --> 14:00.750
They need the rights that go with that.

14:01.916 --> 14:03.833
Stay hidden while we work this out.

14:04.666 --> 14:05.750
Excuse me.

14:09.875 --> 14:11.375
Wait, Ms. Pantazis?

14:12.958 --> 14:15.750
The longer we stay hidden,
the more likely we get caught.

14:15.833 --> 14:17.916
We just want to do the right thing.

14:18.416 --> 14:19.958
You can file for asylum status.

14:20.041 --> 14:22.958
Asylum?
No, no, we are immigrants, not refugees.

14:24.458 --> 14:25.458
Hmm?

14:25.541 --> 14:27.250
There was no war where we came from.

14:27.333 --> 14:29.208
If there was, we'd be refugees,
but there wasn't.

14:29.291 --> 14:32.333
Then find legal work.
Stop using temp agencies.

14:32.916 --> 14:36.708
Find a job that puts you on payroll
and gets you a Social Security number.

14:36.791 --> 14:39.041
That will qualify you for a work permit.

14:39.125 --> 14:40.625
You can open a bank account.

14:40.708 --> 14:44.500
We can take all that and present
a strong residency application, hmm?

14:45.083 --> 14:46.125
Ms. Pantazis,

14:47.291 --> 14:51.208
no one will give us a payroll job
without legal residency.

14:51.708 --> 14:55.250
And no one will give us residency
without a payroll job.

15:08.916 --> 15:09.916
Okay…

15:11.708 --> 15:13.958
Maybe sunglasses.

15:16.625 --> 15:18.250
Watch your brother, eh?

15:21.583 --> 15:23.500
You're not buying for you, Gianni.

15:23.583 --> 15:26.250
I know,
but how will I know people will like it

15:26.333 --> 15:29.000
and want to buy it
if I don't like it first?

15:29.083 --> 15:30.875
You're absolutely right.

15:30.958 --> 15:33.833
You have to believe in what you sell.

15:34.541 --> 15:37.458
But how about you keep this one
for you, huh?

15:38.625 --> 15:40.458
We buy only what we can sell.

15:41.083 --> 15:44.041
Sunglasses are good. Watches and--

15:44.125 --> 15:48.875
Alex, Kostas,
these rosary beads sell very well.

15:51.625 --> 15:53.125
Hi, would you like a--

15:54.083 --> 15:55.250
Excuse me?

15:56.708 --> 15:58.000
Anyone? Anyone?

16:00.833 --> 16:02.000
All right.

16:06.083 --> 16:07.708
They won't stop for me.

16:07.791 --> 16:09.291
They won't even look at me.

16:09.375 --> 16:10.625
Let me teach you something.

16:10.708 --> 16:12.708
The direct approach
might not work for you.

16:12.791 --> 16:14.625
You're not as handsome as me.

16:14.708 --> 16:17.333
Wait. Wait. Wait. Wait.
Trust your big brother.

16:18.000 --> 16:19.000
You can't accept no.

16:19.083 --> 16:20.375
No means maybe.

16:20.458 --> 16:22.208
You're not selling this.
You're selling you.

16:22.291 --> 16:25.000
You have to find out
what each person is interested in.

16:25.750 --> 16:28.416
My brother sells
the best sunglasses in Greece!

16:33.250 --> 16:34.250
Huh?

16:34.333 --> 16:37.125
For you, two euros. Just two euro.

16:37.791 --> 16:40.625
Alex, Kostas, stay closer.

16:49.625 --> 16:51.208
-Look at this.
-Where did you get all of this?

16:51.291 --> 16:53.000
-We sold all our stuff.
-All of it?

16:53.083 --> 16:54.791
-Yes.
-Where's your hat?

16:54.875 --> 16:57.333
-I sold that too.
-Oh, my goodness.

16:58.625 --> 16:59.875
Mama, police!

17:07.500 --> 17:09.458
-Ugo, leave it.
-We can't leave all this!

17:09.541 --> 17:10.666
Rotimi, grab Kostas!

17:15.166 --> 17:16.375
Mom!

17:16.875 --> 17:18.458
Ugo! Rotimi!

18:05.000 --> 18:06.750
-I am winning!

18:07.375 --> 18:09.375
Right. You click it now.

18:11.291 --> 18:13.791
Mama, I can't see! Thano's going to score!

18:13.875 --> 18:14.875
Sorry, Ugo.

18:14.958 --> 18:16.625
He's gonna score anyway.

18:20.541 --> 18:21.666
Over there!

18:27.666 --> 18:29.916
-My boys!
-Papa!

18:30.000 --> 18:31.000
-Oh, yeah?
-Papa!

18:31.083 --> 18:33.166
Four to one! I will defeat you all.

18:33.250 --> 18:34.791
I will defeat you all.

18:34.875 --> 18:38.083
Oh, no! I grossly misjudged the situation.

18:40.500 --> 18:43.000
Okay, let me go and say hello
and goodbye to Mommy.

18:44.875 --> 18:46.333
-Oh! Ow.

18:46.416 --> 18:48.583
-I need the ball! Now!
-Mommy.

18:48.666 --> 18:49.666
Oh, no.

18:50.791 --> 18:52.500
You bought a soccer ball?

18:52.583 --> 18:53.875
Eh, the old one burst.

18:56.333 --> 18:58.125
I need to buy groceries.

18:58.208 --> 18:59.541
We also have to pay rent.

18:59.625 --> 19:00.875
Bamidele wants it today.

19:00.958 --> 19:03.041
Ah. Don't worry. I didn't spend too much.

19:05.125 --> 19:06.291
I promise.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.500
Are you going to tell them
they can't have it? Hmm?

19:12.583 --> 19:14.958
-Pass it.
-Pass it. Pass it! Pass it!

19:15.041 --> 19:16.750
-Pass it!

19:17.791 --> 19:19.083
Pass it! Pass it!

19:19.166 --> 19:21.666
-I'll shop smart. We'll be okay.
-Pass to me! Pass to me!

19:21.750 --> 19:22.750
Okay.

19:22.833 --> 19:24.666
I have to go to work now. I'll be late.

19:24.750 --> 19:25.750
Uh-uh.

19:26.708 --> 19:29.125
-I'll miss you.
-Pass to me. Pass it to me.

19:30.500 --> 19:33.375
